Strings

### Topics Covered:
```python
# STRING CREATION
str1 = 'Hello'
str2 = "World"
str3 = '''Multi-line
string here'''

# INDEXING
text = "Python"
print(text[0])    # P (positive index)
print(text[-1])   # n (negative index)

# SLICING
print(text[0:3])   # Pyt (index 0 to 2)
print(text[::2])   # Pto (skip by 2)
print(text[::-1])  # nohtyP (reverse)

# LENGTH
print(len(text))   # 6

# STRING METHODS
message = "hello world"
print(message.upper())       # HELLO WORLD
print(message.lower())       # hello world
print(message.capitalize())  # Hello world
print(message.title())       # Hello World
print(message.find("world")) # 6
print(message.count("l"))    # 3
print(message.replace("world", "python"))
print(message.startswith("hello"))  # True
print(message.endswith("world"))    # True

# CHAINING METHODS
result = "  hello  ".strip().upper().replace("HELLO", "HI")
print(result)  # HI

# ESCAPE SEQUENCES
print("Hello\nWorld")     # New line
print("Hello\tWorld")     # Tab space
print("She said \"Hi\"")  # Quotes
print("Path: C:\\Users")  # Backslash

# F-STRINGS
name = "John"
age = 25
print(f"My name is {name} and I am {age} years old.")
print(f"Next year I'll be {age + 1}")
```


